data.enText: to have a strong, unpleasant smell
It stinks of smoke in here.

data.chText: 让人觉得很糟糕；令人厌恶；似乎有不正当行为
data.enText: to seem very bad, unpleasant or dishonest

data.chText: 这件事从头到尾都有腐败嫌疑。
data.enText: The whole business stank of corruption.

data.chText: “你觉得这个主意怎么样？”“我觉得是个馊主意。”
data.enText: ‘What do you think of the idea?’ ‘I think it stinks .’

data.chText: 使充满臭味（或难闻气味）
data.enText: to fill a place with a strong, unpleasant smell
the stink of sweat and urine
a lot of trouble and anger about sth

data.chText: 这件事引起了轩然大波。
data.enText: The whole business caused quite a stink.

data.chText: 假如他们想关闭这所学校，我们就要大闹一场。
data.enText: We'll kick up a stink (= complain a lot and cause trouble) if they try to close the school down.

ex.enText: The rose gave off a sweet smell.

ex.chText: 油漆味几天后就会消失。
ex.enText: The smell of the paint will pass off in a few days.

synonyms.bx: 普通用词，指任何通过嗅觉器官感受到的气味，可以是好闻的或难闻的。

ex.chText: 空气中满是玫瑰花的香味。
ex.enText: The air is full of the fragrance of roses.

ex.chText: 丁香散发出芬芳的香味。
ex.enText: The lilac gave off a sweet fragrance.

synonyms.bx: 指怡人的气味，尤指鲜花等散发出的香气。

ex.chText: 这种液体有种特别难闻的气味。
ex.enText: This liquid has an extremely unpleasant odour.

ex.chText: 这种食品散发出叫人难以忍受的气味。
ex.enText: This kind of food gave off an unbearable odour.

ex.chText: 它会明确地告诉我们在你的房间里有什么气味。
ex.enText: It will tell us specifically what odours are found in your room.

synonyms.bx: 指易于辨别的强烈气味，多指难闻的臭味，常用于科技文章中。

ex.enText: The scent of lemons filled the hall.
The breeze wafted with scents of the grass.

ex.chText: 猎犬循着臭迹追踪猎物。
ex.enText: The hounds followed their game by scent.

synonyms.bx: 指某物的香味，或人、动物身上散发出的气味。

ex.chText: 空气中充满了烂鱼的臭味。
ex.enText: The air is full of the stink of decayed fish.

ex.chText: 你可以闻到死尸的臭味。
ex.enText: You can smell the stink of the dead body.

ex.chText: 那臭味都快把我熏死了。
ex.enText: The stink nearly blew my head off.

data.chText: 使充满臭味（或难闻气味）
data.enText: to fill a place with a strong, unpleasant smell

tr: a distinctive odor that is offensively unpleasant
be extremely bad in quality or in one's performance

value.def: To stink means to smell extremely unpleasant.

example.ex: Get away from me —your breath stinks...
The place stinks of fried onions...
example.tran: 这个地方有股煎洋葱的刺鼻气味。

example.ex: The pond stank like a sewer.
example.tran: 池塘像阴沟一样散发着恶臭。

example.ex: He was aware of the stink of stale beer on his breath...
example.tran: 他知道自己嘴里有股变味啤酒的馊味。

value.tran: 发出恶臭;散发难闻气味

example.ex: They were locked up in a stinking cell.
example.tran: 他们被关在一个臭烘烘的牢房里。

value.def: If you say that something stinks, you mean that you disapprove of it because it involves ideas, feelings, or practices that you do not like.

example.tran: 我认为他们的方法糟透了。

example.ex: The whole thing stinks of political corruption.
example.tran: 整件事情都透着政治腐败的气息。

value.tran: 令人讨厌;让人反感;让人感觉糟糕

value.def: If someone makes a stink about something they are angry about, they show their anger in order to make people take notice.

example.ex: The family's making a hell of a stink...
The tabloid press kicked up a stink about his seven-day visit.
example.tran: 小报的报道引起民众对他为期 7 天的访问的强烈不满。

value.tran: (引人注意的)发怒，大吵大闹，泄愤

trans: 臭弹(破碎时发出恶臭，用于恶作剧)
